UML:TaggedValue.value: This concept represents a means of identifying and locating a resource, such as a place, physical location or email box. Common addresses include a postal address, email address and even a telephone number. Revisions applied to entire Contact and Place Package per Information Model Working Group review 1Q 2012. Refer to 5 April 2012 working group meeting minutes and related draft diagram for details. Highlights include: (1) changed from abstract to concrete [PlaceAddress], (2) added classes: [IntersectionAddress], [StreetAddress].

A bounded area defined by nature, by one or a series of country elements, by an external authority (such as a government), used to identify a location in space; for example, country, city, continent, postal area or risk area.e.g. land parcel 5, section 12, lot 3e.g. coastal waterse.g. Hawthorne, NY Postal area, ZIP code 10532e.g. Hurricane risk areae.g. Manhattan, New York Revisions applied to entire Contact and Place Package per Information Model Working Group review 1Q 2012. Refer to 5 April 2012 working group meeting minutes and related draft diagram for details. Highlights include: (1) added class [Municipality], (2) deprecated classes: [CountryElement], [City], [Zone].
The standard abbreviation or code for the geographic area.e.g: NY
The time period at which the place is available for use.
A textual statement used to help identify a place.e.g: Belgium is a small country located on the European coast of the North Sea, bordered by the Netherlands, Germany, France and Luxembourg.
General name given to the location in space (Place).
The measurement of the area of this place.e.g. 400 square kilometers

This relationship links a registration with the place of issuance (e.g. the place to which the granting of rights, privileges, favors, statuses, or qualifications applies as intended by the registry and registry authority).

This relationship links an assessment result with assessed place (e.g. the place as the subject of an assessment result).e.g: The Ohio river valley area is the subject of the condition "flooded".e.g: Lake Erie is affected by the condition "polluted".
This relationship links a residency with a geographic place. Added association.
This relationship links a rating territory to a place.
This relationship links the legal status of an organization to the related place (e.g. country, state, province, etc.).

This relationship links an agreement or agreement component to the place which governs it (e.g. the place which acts as its jurisdiction).Examples:A tax deduction is governed by a place (e.g. country, state, etc.) with regards to tax regulations.An insurance policy is governed by a place (e.g. country, state, etc.) with regards to regulatory requirements. Re-directed association (prior: [TaxDeduction] to [Place]).
This relationship links a citizenship with a geographic place. Added association.
This relationship links a catastrophe registration with one or more affected places.
This relationship (when applicable) links a language to a place (e.g. geographic region) in support of the specific region that identifies a language dialect. Added association.
This relationship links a nationality with a geographic place. Added association.
This relationship links a party's fiscal domicile to a place.
This relationship links a particular loss occurrence with a geographic place.e.g. Fire occurred at the office building located at 15th and Elm.
This relationship links a catastrophe category to one or more places where the catastrophe occurred (e.g. the place recognized by the catastrophe category).
This relation links a market place to one or more geographic places as a list of distribution areas. It defines and identifies, for a market place, the corresponding distribution areas.
This relationship links an event to the place where the event occurred.
This relationship links a registry authority to one or more places of jurisdiction.

This relationship links a product association with one or more places to which the relationship is limited.e.g: The coverage specification for earthquake coverage is not available in the state of Montana.
This relationship links a physical object role with a place.

UML:AssociationEnd.name: Included Physical Object Role On Place

UML:TaggedValue.value: This relationship links a proximity with a place from.

This relationship links an event to the place(s) affected by the event.For example, the volcanic eruption (natural event) of Iceland's Eyjafjallajokull volcano in 2010 affected several places (countries) in Europe. Added association.
This relationship links the operations of an organization to the related place (e.g. country, state, province, etc.). Added association.
This relationship links a tax to the place which governs the tax (e.g. country, state, etc.). Added association.
This relationship links a proximity with a place to.

This relationship links a place with the address that can be utilized to identify or locate the place.For example, the corresponding address might involve the use of coordinates. Such coordinates are complex because there is more than one coordinate system.A given place can have more than one coordinate (there can be very many for large places). A single coordinate, however, can only refer to a single place.
This relationship links an ActivityPlace to a geographic place.
